{% extends 'main.html.twig' %}


{% block section_requirements %}
    <!-- Requirements -->
    <section id="requirements">
        <div class="container">
            <h3>Requirements</h3>
            <p>Imanee needs an underlying image extension like <strong>Imagick</strong> in order to work. Imanee currently supports <strong>Imagick</strong> and <strong>GD</strong> extensions.
            Notice that some features (like animated gifs - not supported by GD) might not be present depending on the extension used.</p>
            <p>Imanee will use an <em>ImagickResource</em> as default whenever the <em>Imagick extension</em> is available. If <em>Imagick</em>
            can't be found, Imanee will try to use a <em>GDResource</em> instead. You can also provide a custom <em>ImageResource</em>
            object while instantiating Imanee.</p>

            <p>Imanee requires <strong>PHP >= 5.4</strong>.</p>

            <h3>Installing the extensions</h3>
            <p>Imagick is the most recommended extension because it has more features, but if you don't need animated gifs you can safely choose to use GD.</p>

            <h4>Ubuntu</h4>

            <p><code>$ sudo apt-get install php5-imagick</code> [ Imagick ]</p>
            <p><code>$ sudo apt-get install php5-gd</code> [ GD ]</p>

            <h4>Related links:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="http://tecadmin.net/install-imagemagick-on-linux/">Installing Imagick on CentOS, RHEL and Ubuntu</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://ma.ttias.be/install-gd-library-for-php5-on-centos/">Installing GD on CentOS</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://refreshless.com/blog/imagick-pecl-imagemagick-windows/">Installing Imagick on Windows</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://www.dmxzone.com/go/5001/how-do-i-install-gd-in-windows/">Installing GD on Windows</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p><small>Don't forget to restart the web server so the changes take effect.</small></p>
        </div>
    </section>
{% endblock %}

{% block section_two %}
<!-- Two -->
<section id="getting-started">
    <div class="container">
        <h3>Getting Started</h3>
        <p>Once you have one of the supported image extensions installed, you can easily add Imanee to your project
        using <a href="https://getcomposer.org/" target="_blank" title="Composer">Composer</a>:</p>

        <p><code>$ composer require imanee/imanee</code></p>

        <h4>Using the default ImageResource</h4>
        <p>Imanee will check if you have the Imagick extension, since that's the default. If it cannot find the extension loaded, it will try to use GD instead.
        An exception will be thrown if you don't have any available.</p>
<pre><code class="php">$imanee = new Imanee('test.jpg');
 echo $imanee->thumbnail(200, 200, true)
        ->output();
</code></pre>

        <h4>Providing an ImageResource</h4>
        <p>Useful when you have Imagick installed but you want to use GD instead. You might also want to create your own ImageResource and use it with Imanee.</p>
<pre><code class="php">$imanee = new Imanee('test.jpg', new GDResource());
echo $imanee->thumbnail(200, 200, true)
        ->output();
    </code></pre>

    </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}
